---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does a Darwin termite inspection cost in 2026?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Typical 2026 Greater Darwin bands: AS 3660.2 annual inspection $320–$480 (most homes $360–$420 — slightly above southern capitals because Top End inspections require sub-floor crawl in stumps-on-piers homes and roof-void inspections at 35–40°C wet-season temperatures). AS 4349.3 pre-purchase inspection (written report for settlement) $480–$680. Structural-and-pest combined $700–$950. Chemical soil barrier (Termidor SC or Premise 200SC) $2,800–$6,500 typical, up to $12K for rural acreage with reticulation tube around outbuildings. Sentricon Always Active baiting install $2,000–$3,800 + ~$420/yr monitoring. Pre-construction barrier on a new build $2,200–$4,200. Active Mastotermes infestation treatment varies widely — $3,500 for a small contained colony up to $30K+ for whole-of-structure rebuild remediation. Rural Litchfield Council properties cost ~15–20% more than urban Darwin due to travel time and acreage perimeter length." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why is Darwin termite risk so high compared to southern Australia?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Three reasons. (1) Mastotermes darwiniensis — the world's most destructive termite — is endemic north of about 19°S latitude. Greater Darwin sits squarely inside Mastotermes country. Unlike Coptotermes, Mastotermes will eat almost anything: timber, paper, leather, plastic, soft metals (lead flashing, copper pipe insulation), rubber, even concrete with high lime content. (2) Tropical climate = year-round activity. No winter slowdown like Melbourne or even Brisbane. Soil temperature stays above 25°C for 9+ months and rarely dips below 20°C, so colonies forage continuously. (3) Building stock is unusually termite-vulnerable: high-set timber on stumps (sub-floor moisture + timber bearers), older fibro houses with unreticulated slabs, post-Cyclone-Tracy rebuilds (1975–1985 timber framing now 40–50 years old, well past any original chemical barrier), and rural acreage at Howard Springs / Humpty Doo / Berry Springs where Mastotermes colonies can be 200–300m away in surrounding bush." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What's the difference between Mastotermes and Coptotermes in the Top End?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Both are present in Greater Darwin and both cause major damage, but they behave very differently. Coptotermes acinaciformis is the species most pest controllers train on in southern Australia — it builds large central colonies (often inside a tree trunk), sends foraging tubes through soil, and prefers softer timbers. You'll find it in urban Darwin (Casuarina, Nightcliff, Stuart Park) as much as elsewhere in Australia. Mastotermes darwiniensis is in a separate evolutionary line — it's the only living member of its family, considered the most primitive termite still alive. It forms diffuse subterranean colonies that can spread across 1–2 hectares. It chews through concrete with high lime content, soft metals, rubber and plastic to get to cellulose. It's especially common in rural Top End acreage and along bushland boundaries. We treat both. The treatment approach differs — Mastotermes responds well to bait but needs deeper soil-injection volumes than Coptotermes because the colony footprint is wider." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does the NT Building Act require termite barriers on new homes?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. The NT Building Regulations adopt the National Construction Code (NCC) Volume Two, which makes AS 3660.1 compliance mandatory for primary building elements on every new Class 1 (dwelling) and Class 10 (outbuilding) build. The certifier won't sign off the Form 21 occupation certificate without the Termite Management Certificate (Form 16 or equivalent) showing the AS 3660.1 system installed — typically chemical reticulation under the slab + perimeter chemical-soil treatment, OR a physical barrier (Kordon, HomeGuard) + perimeter chemical-soil, OR a baiting system with documented installation. Renovations that disturb the slab penetrations or perimeter require reinstatement of the barrier. We do the pre-construction barriers + issue the Form 16 paperwork builders need for handover." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Darwin Termite Barriers | Mastotermes & Coptotermes Inspections, Soil Barriers, Baiting | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Top End termite specialists across Greater Darwin — Mastotermes darwiniensis, Coptotermes acinaciformis and Schedorhinotermes inspection, chemical-soil barriers (Termidor SC + Premise 200SC) and Sentricon baiting. AS 3660.1 pre-construction, AS 3660.2 annual, AS 4349.3 pre-purchase. NT Pest Control licensed.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Palmerston &middot; Casuarina &middot; Nightcliff &middot; Humpty Doo &middot; Howard Springs</span>
      <h1>Top End specialists in <span class="accent">Mastotermes &amp; Coptotermes</span> termite barriers.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        AS 3660.2 annual inspections. AS 4349.3 pre-purchase inspections for
        property settlement. AS 3660.1 pre-construction barriers + Form 16
        certification. Termidor SC and Premise 200SC chemical-soil treatments.
        Sentricon Always Active, Exterra and Trelona baiting. Greater Darwin,
        Palmerston, and rural Litchfield Council &mdash; Casuarina to Humpty Doo.
        NT Pest Control licensed. AEPMA member.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book an inspection</a>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-trust">
        <div><strong>AS 3660.1</strong>Pre-construction barrier</div>
        <div><strong>AS 3660.2</strong>In-service inspection</div>
        <div><strong>AS 4349.3</strong>Pre-purchase report standard</div>
        <div><strong>AEPMA</strong>Industry-body member</div>
